##  Enterprise Architecture: The City Planning of IT

Think of our IT environment like a smart city. Every new application, like OpenMRS, is a new building â€“ it must connect to the **roads (networks)**, **utilities (logging, security, backups)**, and **identity systems (SSO/LDAP)**. You wouldnâ€™t put up a skyscraper without checking the zoning laws or where the power lines are â€“ and the same goes for enterprise systems.

In my clinic scenario, OpenMRS doesnâ€™t stand alone â€“ itâ€™s part of an AWS-based digital healthcare ecosystem.

